
[1]optative

   OP'TATIVE, a. [L. optativus, from opto, to desire or wish.]

   Expressing desire or wish. The optative mode, in grammar, is that form
   of the verb in which wish or desire is expressed.

            OP'TATIVE, n. Something to be desired. [Little used.]
